{
  "text": "The q-2q scans indicate that the as-deposited YSZ \ue103lms are textured in Fig. 2. However, Fig. 6 and 7 , u or rocking curve ). * indicates peaks from Si substrate, the 33 peak is for the forbidden 200 reflection, whereas the 61 peak is for the 400 reflection due to Cukb radiation. A summary of the variation in FWHM with growth stress (s g ) of the YSZ \ue103lms is shown in Fig. 8(b) . It shows that the FWHM of the rocking curve decrease from [CITATION_1] to 16 with growth rates ranging from 30 to 0.8 nm min \u00c01 for (100) and (111) YSZ \ue103lms respectively. This is due to compressive stress driven annealing during growth which will discussed in detail as we go along. Thus, (100) \ue103lms are more defective than (111) \ue103lms as (100) YSZ \ue103lms show larger FWHM than (111) \ue103lms. A measure of how defective these oxide \ue103lms are can be gauged from the fact that the as-deposited rocking curve widths of epitaxial IIInitride \ue103lms on Si are routinely in the 0.1-1 range.",
